he office for the remainder of the term that ends in January. The special election offers its winner a possible advantage in November and, if elected then, seniority over 30 to 40 incoming freshmen House members in January. During the current campaign, <PERSON> Ellis </PERSON> stressed his political experience and education. He has served 13 years on the <ORGANIZATION> Aldermanic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> and has masters' degrees in public administration and education administration. The Costello camp promised to work for economic development, for protection of the Social Security system and against drugs.
