<HEAD>Duarte, Defying Cancer, Gets Back to Work</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DOUGLAS GRANT MINE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Defying terminal cancer, President <PERSON> Jose </PERSON> <PERSON> Napoleon </PERSON> <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON> returned from <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> to begin catching up on official business after six weeks' absence. `` I am here now to reassume the presidency, in order to continue working for what I most love: democracy,'' the 62-year-old <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON> said upon arriving Monday from the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> capital, where he underwent diagnosis and treatment beginning May 31. `` I certainly am not cured. But I am strong. I have the capacity and the strength to carry out both the medical requisites my disease demands and my work for the people,'' said <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON>, the <LOCATION> Western </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hemisphere </LOCATION>' staunchest <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> ally. <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON>, whose five-year term ends June 1, 1989, was leaner than when he left and his face was somewhat drawn. But his step was firm and his embrace appeared strong as he greeted <PERSON> Rodolfo </PERSON> <PERSON> Castillo </PERSON> <PERSON> Claramount </PERSON>, the vice president and acting chief executive, and other officials on the tarmac of <LOCATION> Ilopango </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION> outside the capital. After a brief airport ceremony, he was driven to the presidential residence to rest. The chemotherapy <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON> is undergoing for liver cancer has debilitated him somewhat, but he vowed the illness would not keep him down. Doctors have given him between six and 18 months to live. <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON> promised to continue working with the military against leftist guerrillas `` in order to bring peace to my people ... in that way I will make it to the first of June and hand power over to the one who is elected by the people.'' <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON>'s governing <ORGANIZATION> Christian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> is in