</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Wanted: good homes for $ 10,000 worth of shampoo, hair conditioner and bath gel in 97,900 little packets. The Fairmont Hotel is getting rid of those packets that grace many hotel bathrooms as part of its preparations for the Republican National Convention. `` We replaced them ... with superior plastic bottles,'' said hotel spokesman <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> De </PERSON> <PERSON> Mers </PERSON>. `` What makes them superior, of course, is you do n't have to rip them open with your teeth and get shampoo in your mouth. And you can get two or three shampoos out of one bottle. Plus people love to take them home as souvenirs.'' De Mers had two questions when the hotel chain's <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION> headquarters ordered him to get rid of the packets: how many were there, and who should they go to? It took time to answer the first question. `` I got someone to lead me to the shampoo and started counting. And I counted and I counted and I counted,'' De Mers said Monday. It turned out there were 38,500 packets of shampoo, 54,900 of hair conditioner and 4,500 of bath gel. There still was the question of who should get them. `` You can give food to the foodless and homes to the homeless, but who do you give shampoo to?'' he asked. So the hotel is holding a Send Us The Suds contest, with Aug. 15 _ the day the <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Convention </ORGANIZATION> gavels down in the Superdome _ as the deadline for two-page written entries explaining how much shampoo, conditioner or bath gel is wanted, and what it's wanted for `` I would have to say that the more unexpected the reason, the better,'' said <ORGANIZATION> De </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mers </ORGANIZATION>. `` We're looking purposely for needs that we ca n't possibly anticipate. People should n't stop entering if they have a fairly strange reason they need the shampoo. It may just make them a winner.''
