<HEAD>Demo Ticket Has Two Millionaires</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RITA BEAMISH</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 With <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>' selection of <PERSON> Lloyd </PERSON> <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON> as his running mate, the 1988 Democratic presidential ticket will consist of two millionaires. <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON> has a personal worth estimated at $ 1.4 million to $ 2 million, according to financial disclosure forms on file in public records. The <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> senator is also a prolific campaign fund raiser who ran into controversy last year with a practice of collecting $ 10,000 apiece from lobbyists who ate breakfast with him once a month. After press reports surfaced about the `` breakfast club,'' <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON> acknowledged in February 1987 that he had made a `` doozy'' of a mistake in forming such a club. <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON> had solicited members to his `` Chairman's Council'' by sending letters to 200 political action committees and lobbyists telling them he was seeking advice and assistance for his campaign. On his personal financial statement this year, which is separate from the campaign fund, <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON> listed income of between $ 296,733 and $ 418,225 and up. The forms are designed in a manner that does not require disclosure of a specific amount. His assets included a <ORGANIZATION> Warwick </ORGANIZATION> condominium and furnishings in <LOCATION> Houston </LOCATION>, a qualified blind trust from which he received at least $ 100,001 in interest last year, a note to <LOCATION> Brazoria </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lake </LOCATION> inc. of <LOCATION> Brazoria </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, and <ORGANIZATION> Bellfield </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Farm </ORGANIZATION> on the <LOCATION> Shenandoah </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Clarke </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON> was born into wealth His father, `` Big Lloyd'' <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON>, migrated to the <LOCATION> Rio </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Grande </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION> after World War I and made himself wealthy as a rancher and by buying land and reselling it. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> has a net worth of more than $ 500,000 in property, investments and salary, and also is the potential beneficiary of $ 1 million in trusts.
