<BYLINE>By SUE MAJOR HOLMES</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Police with dogs today captured a murderer whose girlfriend allegedly hijacked the helicopter used in an aerial prison breakout that was foiled by other copters after a wild two-hour chase, authorities said. <PERSON> Daniel </PERSON> <PERSON> Mahoney </PERSON>, 30, was caught early this morning near <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lunas </LOCATION> after a corrections officer spotted his trail and called a canine unit, which tracked him along the <LOCATION> Rio </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Grande </LOCATION>, said state police Sgt. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Balderston </PERSON>. The two other Penitentiary of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> inmates who escaped Monday morning with <PERSON> Mahoney </PERSON>, his girlfriend and the pilot also were in custody today. The pilot said he had been hijacked and a friend said he had flown the same helicopter in the movie `` Rambo III.'' Authorities gave this account of the escape attempt, during which a <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Customs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> helicopter was nearly rammed and the escapees allegedly tried to force a state police chopper into a crane: A yellow-and-bronze <ORGANIZATION> Aerospatiale </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Gazelle </ORGANIZATION> helicopter landed in a prison yard about 9:50 a.m. Monday, and the three convicts jumped aboard amid fire from tower guards. One other unidentified convict was forced off or jumped off the chopper, which haad a hard time getting off the ground. A Customs copter and Immigration and <ORGANIZATION> Naturalization </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> airplane chased them 80 miles south to <LOCATION> Mid-Valley </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lunas </LOCATION>, where <PERSON> Mahoney </PERSON>, <PERSON> Randy </PERSON> <PERSON> Mack </PERSON> <PERSON> Lackey </PERSON> and <PERSON> Beverly </PERSON> <PERSON> Shoem