 </PERSON>, owner of Bear Helicopters, was hired by a man who identified himself as a businessman, said his wife, <PERSON> Carrol </PERSON>, in <LOCATION> El </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Paso </LOCATION>. He told his wife that Ms. <PERSON> Shoemaker </PERSON> put a gun to his head and handcuffed him to the control stick. <PERSON> Bella </PERSON>'s <PERSON> Gazelle </PERSON> played the `` Russian'' copter movie star <PERSON> Sylvester </PERSON> <PERSON> Stallone </PERSON> shot down with a explosive-tipped arrow in `` Rambo III,'' said a friend, <PERSON> Tony </PERSON> <PERSON> Mobley </PERSON>. <PERSON> Bella </PERSON> also did stunts in the movie `` Extreme Prejudice.'' Ms. <PERSON> Shoemaker </PERSON>'s name appears on <PERSON> Mahoney </PERSON>'s visitor list and the <LOCATION> Santa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Fe </LOCATION> resident is believed to be his girlfriend, said <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> <PERSON> Taylor </PERSON>, spokesman for the state <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Safety </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Mahoney </PERSON> was serving life plus 60 years for second-degree murder in <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Lackey </PERSON>, 36, was treated in <LOCATION> Albuquerque </LOCATION> for a shoulder wound and returned to the prison, where he was serving nine years for larceny in <LOCATION> Curry </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.M. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mitchell </LOCATION>, 26, was doing life for murder in <LOCATION> Summit </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Utah </LOCATION>. The three escapees had been housed in adjacent cells, and were classified as medium-security prisoners, said state Corrections Secretary O.L. <PERSON> McCotter </PERSON>. <PERSON> Mahoney </PERSON> and <PERSON> Mitchell </PERSON> were being held in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> under an interstate agreement providing for exchang