<BYLINE>By ARLENE LEVINSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Faneuil Hall, the historic building picked by <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> to introduce <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> Sen. <PERSON> Lloyd </PERSON> <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON> as his running mate, has been a centerpiece of both the American Revolution and of a modern economic revival. A box-shaped brick structure with a steeple crowned by a grasshopper weathervane, the Great Hall in <LOCATION> Faneuil </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hall </LOCATION>, as it is formally known, was built in 1742 as a gift to the city by merchant <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Faneuil </PERSON>. It earned the nickname `` The Cradle of Liberty'' as a forum for revolutionaries grousing about the taxation policies of the British Empire and plotting their revolt. Later it was the staging ground for anti-slavery, temperance and women's suffrage rallies. Among speakers who stood there were <PERSON> Frederick </PERSON> <PERSON> Douglass </PERSON>, <PERSON> Daniel </PERSON> <PERSON> Webster </PERSON> and <PERSON> Susan </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON>. Still much in use for public celebrations and political speeches, it was here that Sen. <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Kennedy </PERSON>, D-Mass., announced his candidacy for the presidential nomination in November 1979 <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> has also stood on this stage before. The 900-seat hall just 100 feet from <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Harbor </LOCATION> was the background for some tapings of `` The Advocates,'' a public affairs TV program he moderated in 1970-73, before he became governor of <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION>. The building, owned by the city and maintained by the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Park </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION>, became the anchor of a 1970s refurbishment of the Faneuil Hall Marketplace, a cobblestoned mall of boutiques, food stalls and souvenir vendors. It is one of the nation's most visited