<DATELINE>MANAMA, Bahrain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Two <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> helicopters traded fire with a pair of Iranian gunboats after the boats attacked a tanker in the northern <LOCATION> Persian </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> today, <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> military sources said. The sources, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said there was no damage to the aircraft and it was not known whether the boats were damaged in the clash, which took place at about 7 p.m. The sources said the helicopters, off the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> missile frigate <PERSON> Nicholas </PERSON>, were responding to a distress call from a Panamanian-flag tanker west of <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s <LOCATION> Farsi </LOCATION> island. `` The helicopters took fire from the two small boats and returned fire with rockets,'' said a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> official. `` There was no damage to the helos -LRB- helicopters -RRB-. We have no damage assessment on the boats.'' Shipping executives said the attack on the tanker started a fire in the engine room of the 81,282-ton Universal Monarch, but that the crew put out the blaze on their own and that no one aboard the vessel was injured. It was the second time in less than two weeks that an American warship responded to a distress signal from a neutral ship in the gulf. The previous time was on July 2 in the southern gulf, when another frigate intervened to drive off Iranian speedboats attacking a Danish tanker. The next day, the <ORGANIZATION> USS </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Vincennes </ORGANIZATION> shot down an Iranian passenger jet following an exchange of fire with Iranian boats. <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> said 290 people aboard the plane died. The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> said the plane was shot down in the mistaken belief it was an attacking warplane. The <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> administration has promised to make reparations to the families of the victims. The London-based <ORGANIZATION> Lloyd </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZ