<FIRST>r a AM-PrisonEscape     07-12 0251</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Prison Escape,0258</SECOND>
<HEAD>Inmates Trick Guards With Dummies In Beds</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TUCKER, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Four inmates, two of them convicted murderers, escaped a maximum-security prison after tricking guards by putting dummies made from stuffed long johns in their cots, authorities said Tuesday. Guards twice counted the dummies during overnight bed checks, said prison spokesman <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> White </PERSON>. The inmates went to a laundry area, slid down a homemade rope, and moved along a shallow ditch along a fence not visible from the guard tower, he said. `` At the 7 a.m. count, when there was n't any movement, they were discovered missing,'' <PERSON> White </PERSON> said. It was the first escape from the Maximum Security Unit at <LOCATION> Tucker </LOCATION>, in central <LOCATION> Arkansas </LOCATION>, about 30 miles southeast of <LOCATION> Little </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rock </LOCATION>. <PERSON> White </PERSON> said the dummies were made of white thermal underwear stuffed with blankets. The heads were made of white stocking caps with pieces of human hair taped to them. Two of the four worked in the laundry room, he said. Sgt. <PERSON> Fred </PERSON> <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> Correction </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> said all the inmates were in individual cells. The escapees were identified as convicted murderers <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Ray </PERSON> <PERSON> Renton </PERSON>, 50, and <PERSON> Raymond </PERSON> <PERSON> Coble </PERSON>, 29; <PERSON> Tommy </PERSON> <PERSON> Winberry </PERSON>, 38, convicted of two counts of attempted murder, and <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Fane </PERSON>, 31, convicted of aggravated robbery and other crimes. <PERSON> Coble </PERSON> and <PERSON> Winberry </PERSON> escaped from another state prison in November 1986, <PERSON> White </PERSON> said, but were recaptured a short time later. Authorities were using an airplane, dogs and a roadblock in their search for the escaped inmates.
