<BYLINE>By JAMES ROWLEY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A military tribunal is fighting the <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION>'s attempt to investigate an anonymous allegation that bribery influenced its decision overturning a <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> heart surgeon's convictions for the deaths of three The <ORGANIZATION> Navy-Marine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corps </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Military </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Review </ORGANIZATION> obtained an order from the <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Military </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Appeals </ORGANIZATION> temporarily barring the <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>'s inspector general from proceeding with the investigation. The military appeals court, which originally granted the temporary injunction June 30, extended the order Monday for 15 days pending its final decision in the matter. At issue, says <PERSON> Patrick </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Carome </PERSON>, a lawyer appointed to represent the tribunal, is the independence of military courts from interference by the <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION>'s command hierarchy. `` The judges feel this is a situation in which command influence or at least the appearance of it is being brought to bear'' on the tribunal's unpopular decision to set aside the negligent homicide and involuntary manslaughter convictions of Cmdr. <PERSON> Donal </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Billig </PERSON>, <PERSON> Carome </PERSON> said. On April 13, the <ORGANIZATION> Navy-Marine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corps </ORGANIZATION> tribunal overturned <PERSON> Billig </PERSON>'s conviction and accused <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> prosecutors of waging a `` smear campaign'' against the surgeon, who had practiced at the <ORGANIZATION> Bethesda </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Naval </ORGANIZATION> <ORGA