 was bound, killed with a single bullet through the head and left to rot in a mass grave. The murdered officers had been interned by the Soviets, who accused the Nazis of the massacre. A joint study commission has been established to investigate <LOCATION> Katyn </LOCATION>, but <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON> indicated Monday that he is not yet prepared to draw any concuslions.
