ed. <ORGANIZATION> Coleco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industries </ORGANIZATION> was unchanged at 1 ~ The company announced it had sought protection from creditors under Chapter 11 of the Bankruptcy Code. Xidex rose 1 -RRB- to 9 in over-the-counter trading. The maker of computer disk drives said it agreed to be acquired by <ORGANIZATION> Anacomp </ORGANIZATION> for $ 10 a share in cash. <ORGANIZATION> Anacomp </ORGANIZATION> was off -RCB- to 10 \ on the <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION> Among other over-the-counter stocks, <ORGANIZATION> Intel </ORGANIZATION> was up ~ to 35 -LCB- after reporting its earnings nearly tripled in the latest quarter. Micron Technology was off -RCB- to 23 -LRB- on news that two top officers resigned. The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks fell 0.88 to 152.14. At the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the market value index fell 0.91 to 307.67. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION>, swelled by dividend-related trading, came to 84.17 million shares as of noon on Wall Street, against 64.32 million shares at the same time Monday.
