<HEAD>Merrill Lynch Net Off 36 Percent In Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Merrill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lynch </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> on Tuesday said lower financial activity contributed to a 36 percent drop in its second-quarter profit. <ORGANIZATION> Merrill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lynch </ORGANIZATION>, one of the nation's largest investment houses, said net income totaled $ 53.5 million, or 47 cents a share, in the second quarter, compared with earnings of $ 83.3 million, or 75 cents a share, a year ago. Revenue during the quarter rose 8 percent, to $ 2.5 billion from $ 2.3 billion in the second quarter of 1987. <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Schreyer </PERSON>, chairman and chief executive officer, said the results were `` reasonable considering the difficult business environment experienced during the quarter.'' He said the period was marked by `` a relatively lower level of activity in the financial markets.'' Commission revenues in the second quarter declined 35 percent to $ 393 million `` due to reduced stock market activity,'' the company said in a statement. Investment banking revenue also declined _ down 13 percent to $ 256 million _ reflecting a lower level of mergers and acqusitions closings But record fixed-income activity drove principal transaction revenue to $ 388 million, compared with a loss of $ 133 million a year ago. Insurance revenues of $ 85 million and asset management and custodial fee revenues of $ 122 million were little changed from the previous year. <PERSON> Daniel </PERSON> <PERSON> Tully </PERSON>, president and chief operating officer, said the company is confident `` the cost-control and productivity improvement measures put into place during the first half are on course.'' For the first six months of 1988, net earnings totaled $ 122 million, or $ 1.08, off 36 percent from $ 192 million, or $ 1.72 a share in the first half of 1987. Revenue for the first six months totaled $ 4.9 billion, up 1 percent from $ 4.8 billion in the year-ago period.
